! Mass Number Sidecar Rule

A rule that Mass Number metadata must travel beside implementation surfaces
as a receipt, not mutate the implementation into a self-justifying gate.

!! Why It Matters

It keeps semantic mass useful while preventing routing metadata from corrupting
the code, proof, or artifact it is supposed to evaluate.

